Package: bivnegbincp
Title: Bayesian Change Point Detection for Bivariate Negative Binomial Data
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: 
    c(
      person("Arnoneel", "Sinha", email = "arsinha@augusta.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")),
      person("Kathryn", "Sinha", role = "aut"),
      person("Jie", "Chen", role = "aut")
    )
Description: This package implements a Bayesian change point detection method 
    for sequences of bivariate Negative Binomial observations, extending earlier 
    work on bivariate Normal data. The methodology is motivated by the need to 
    jointly analyze correlated count time series, such as COVID-19 incidence 
    and death data.
    The package provides single change point detection under both constant prior 
    and Dirichlet prior formulations, along with multiple change point detection 
    using a binary segmentation procedure. The approach models the joint 
    distribution of bivariate count observations and identifies structural 
    changes through probabilistic inference.
    The methods are particularly suited for applications involving overdispersed 
    and correlated count data where simultaneous shifts may occur across variables. 
    Visualization tools are included to aid in interpreting detected change points.
